.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:28:Current strict Compare tab count: **1 visible scalar dimension**. `CompareTab` renders one gold stat block, one measured stat block, and one tolerance band from `ValidationReport.gold_standard`/`measurement` (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:897-945`). It does not render a profile, v-centerline, vortex location, stream-function extrema, kinetic energy, wall shear, or a grid-convergence plot. Across the whole `/learn` page, the Story tab embeds a scientific report iframe for LDC (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1840-1919`) and the Mesh tab shows a convergence slider (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1073-1230`), so the student can see more evidence outside Compare. But for independent gold-comparison dimensions, I count **at most 2 across the full page**: u_centerline profile and a grid-convergence trend on one u_centerline sample. Derived metrics such as L2, L∞, RMS, max deviation, and pass count are useful statistics, but they are not independent physics observables.
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:32:| 1. `u_centerline` profile, x=0.5 vertical line | **Yes.** LDC generation writes uCenterline sampling (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:1116-1132`), runtime parsing populates `u_centerline` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7678-7712`), fallback extraction also populates `u_centerline` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7908-7980`), and comparison-report metrics load only the u_centerline doc (`ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:134-154`, `ui/backend/services/comparison_report.py:427-431`). | **Not as a profile in Compare tab.** Compare tab shows scalar stat/tolerance only (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:897-945`). The profile appears in the Story embedded scientific report/iframe, not the Compare tab (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1848-1917`). | **Yes.** `quantity: u_centerline`, 17 y/u values, tolerance, source (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:59-97`). | Move or duplicate profile overlay and pointwise-deviation bar into Compare tab. Also label the scalar anchor's y coordinate clearly because the current stat block hides that the measurement may be a selected point. |
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:33:| 2. `v_centerline` profile, y=0.5 horizontal line | **No live sim extractor.** The LDC branches only populate `u_centerline` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7342-7350`, `src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7457-7462`, `src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7678-7712`). Static public literature plot includes v, but that is not solver extraction (`ui/frontend/src/data/flowFields.ts:19-31`). | **No.** Compare tab's generic stat/tolerance UI has no second profile slot (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:897-945`). | **Present but explicitly suspect.** Header says v_centerline appears mislabeled and uncorrected (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:26-32`); the v document exists (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:115-145`). | First repair gold axis labels to x-based Table II; then add horizontal sample line to `foam_agent_adapter.py`, parser key `v_centerline`, comparator support, render `profile_v_centerline.png`, and Compare tab panel. |
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:35:| 4. Stream-function `ψ_min` primary-vortex strength | **No.** The real render uses velocity streamplot, not computed ψ (`scripts/render_case_report.py:511-520`). The public `stream_function.png` is an ansatz calibrated to profiles, not solver ψ (`ui/frontend/src/data/flowFields.ts:27-30`). | **No.** | **No.** YAML has no ψ observable (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:59-189`). | Add a stream-function post-process step or compute ψ by integrating velocity on the structured grid; add literature value/source and tolerance; render `psi_min` card and contour marker. |
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:58:For validation, the page uses Ghia, Ghia & Shin 1982 as the gold standard. The primary observable is the horizontal velocity along the vertical centerline \(x=0.5\). The simulated \(u/U_{lid}\) profile should be compared to Ghia's tabulated values at multiple \(y/L\) locations. The page says the comparison is important because matching this profile is the first proof that the solver, mesh, boundary conditions, and extraction path are reasonable. The real OpenFOAM report shows a contour with streamlines, a centerline profile plot, a pointwise deviation plot, and a residual convergence plot. The residuals decay to around \(10^{-5}\), so the numerical iteration appears converged. The profile plot indicates that many Ghia points are close, but the pointwise deviation plot reports only 11/17 points inside the 5% tolerance. Therefore I would describe the current result as partially matching Ghia, not a clean validation pass.
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:60:【I don't know】The page does not give me a complete `blockMeshDict`, `0/U`, `0/p`, `fvSchemes`, or `fvSolution`, so I cannot reproduce the run from the page without inventing files. 【I don't know】The workflow says 40x40 cells and `nu=0.01`, but the report figure says 129x129 and the generator uses `convertToMeters 0.1` with `nu=0.001`; I do not know which setup belongs in my course report. 【I don't know】The observable card says v-centerline and primary-vortex location are supported, but the current Compare tab only gives me one scalar tolerance band and the gold YAML warns that v-centerline and vortex center are not corrected. I cannot honestly claim five validation dimensions. 【Page doesn't say】I do not know how to compute the stream function, vortex strength, secondary vortex positions, integrated kinetic energy, or wall shear stress. 【Page doesn't say】I do not know how to cite the synthetic stream-function image versus the real OpenFOAM contour, or why the synthetic picture looks more symmetric than the real contour. Because of these gaps, the report can describe the physical story and one u-centerline comparison, but it cannot yet be a full reproducibility/validation report.
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:67:- 🔴 **Raise Compare tab from scalar to multi-dimensional evidence.** Modify `CompareTab` (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:792-947`) to show at least the LDC u profile, pointwise deviation bars, and grid-convergence trend directly, not only the scalar tolerance band. Then add v-centerline and vortex center once gold/extractor are fixed. The Story iframe is not enough; the tab named Compare must be where comparison lives.
.planning/reviews/case_pilot_ldc_findings.md:72:- 🟠 **Add a novice glossary.** Under the physical intuition block (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:405-415`), add definitions for SIMPLE, URF, residual, stream function, vortex center, GCI, and tolerance band. Keep this short, but make every term used in `learnCases.ts:136-141` discoverable without Googling.
