.planning/decisions/2026-04-23_cfd_bfs_adapter_geometry_finding_dec051.md:33:Added a BFS velocity_streamlines.png rendered from the existing audit VTK at reports/phase5_fields/backward_facing_step/20260421T125637Z/VTK/ldc_88913_1776776197258_36.vtk. Annotated measured Xr/H=3.77 vs Ghia/LMK gold 6.26 (-39.8%), labeled the deviation as "mesh-resolution artifact from the 800-cell ATTEST_HAZARD fixture", promoted the figure to `kind: solver_output` in flowFields.ts.
.planning/decisions/2026-04-23_cfd_bfs_adapter_geometry_finding_dec051.md:42:1. **Probe-height sensitivity (trying to falsify my own method)**. Ran the Xr extractor at y = 0.010, 0.020, 0.028, 0.056 on the same fixture. All four returned Xr/H ≈ 3.82 (identical to 6 significant figures). My original y=0.02 choice was stable — the probe-height issue I asked Codex about was a red herring. Good.
.planning/decisions/2026-04-23_cfd_bfs_adapter_geometry_finding_dec051.md:47:   - Inlet BC audit: `src/foam_agent_adapter.py::_generate_backward_facing_step` (lines 1465-1495) sets `0/U inlet: fixedValue uniform (U_bulk 0 0)` over the **entire inlet face** (not just y > 1). There is also no step baked into the BC profile.
.planning/decisions/2026-04-23_cfd_bfs_adapter_geometry_finding_dec051.md:55:- BFS has **no step geometry at all**. The "Xr = 3.77" is not a low-SNR reattachment measurement; it is a zero-crossing in diverged boundary-cell data on a flat channel. No amount of mesh refinement on the current generator template will produce a real BFS flow.
.planning/decisions/2026-04-23_cfd_bfs_adapter_geometry_finding_dec051.md:60:If I had left it in place, the /learn/backward_facing_step Story tab would have shown a "real solver" velocity-streamlines figure claiming -39.8% deviation is a "mesh-resolution artifact". A student reading it would have formed the mental model:
