    86	
    87	### Batch C · Codex round 1 + iterate
    88	
    89	After Batches A+B are committed and pushed, invoke Codex via `/codex-gpt54` with these review dimensions (mirroring the LDC V61-050 pattern):
    90	
    91	1. Geometry correctness — re-verify the 3-block topology matches what the physics needs
    92	2. Convergence — residual log analysis (A1-A6 attestor), URF choices, max iterations
    93	3. Xr extraction — verify the near-wall probe locates reattachment in the true sign-change of U_x(y→0), not just the first zero in a coarse probe
    94	4. SNR argument — what's the equivalent of LDC D8's SNR check for BFS? Wall-shear variability across coarse cells; if Xr is extracted from a region with cell width > Xr_signal, we have the same "signal below noise" failure mode
    95	5. Tolerance defensibility — 10% on Xr/H=6.26 vs the Le/Moin/Kim 6.28 / Driver 6.26 bracket at Re=7600
    96	6. Figure honesty — if the new fixture has a meaningful Xr within tolerance, label as `solver_output`; otherwise stay honest about residual deviation
    97	
    98	Iterate on findings. Retraction is allowed and expected — the LDC precedent was 1 HIGH + 4 MED + 1 LOW in round 1. Success metric: VERDICT is APPROVE or APPROVE_WITH_COMMENTS with all HIGHs fixed.
    99	
   100	### Batch D · LDC-style visualization + Compare-tab integration (blocked on A+B+C)
   101	
   102	Only after Codex APPROVE_WITH_COMMENTS on the new fixture:
   103	
   104	- Regenerate `/flow-fields/backward_facing_step/velocity_streamlines.png` from the new VTK (same script path as the reverted 4e4813f, but pointing at the new timestamp and with any Codex-surfaced fixes applied).
